1340. Nov. 13. [On a proposed exchange between Hem-y de Schypton‚ rector of Leigh, and

Roger de Frendesbery, rector of Stradishall (Suffolk)‚ the bishop on Sept. 23 issued a commission to the archdeacon of Rochester to make the usual inquisition. This was returned, dated Oct. 4. The bishop on Oct. 6 commissioned Master Adam de Murimouth, canon of London, to effect the exchange, and Adam’s certificate was returned, dated Nov. 12. The next day Roger de Frendesbery made his oath of obedience and the mandate sor his induction was issued.]
